Management Discussion & Analysis
Apex delivered record results in 2024, driven by the successful launch of the Aurora cloud analytics platform and expanded enterprise license agreements across the EMEA region. Gross margins improved 80 basis points to 44.6%, reflecting disciplined cost management and scale efficiencies. Operating expenses grew in line with revenue as we continued to invest in AI-driven product features and global sales capacity. Net income was impacted by a non-cash impairment charge of $18M related to the legacy data hosting unit, which is scheduled for divestiture in Q2 2025.

Future Outlook
We expect 2025 revenue growth of 10-12% at constant currency, supported by a $2.1B qualified pipeline and three strategic product launches in cybersecurity analytics. Capital expenditures are forecasted at approximately $310M as we build out our Frankfurt and Singapore data centers. The Board has authorized a $500M share repurchase program starting Q2 2025. We remain attentive to macroeconomic headwinds in APAC, particularly elongated procurement cycles in the banking vertical.

